issue.title: cpufeatures: do not prevent inlining
issue.body:
I suspect that `#[inline(never)]` is used for performance reasons, but maybe something like `#[cold]` is sufficient for the same purpose? `#[cold]` is what `once_cell` is using in performance-sensitive places for example.

It is causing issues for me with https://github.com/dtolnay/no-panic, which relies on inlining and `cpufeatures` is the only thing using `#[inline(never)]` in multiple cases where platform-dependent code is present.

issue.title: Try to improve compatibility with other garage mods + remove/change some hooks
issue.body:
List of changes I made, probably incomplete, I didn't keep track of them all:
- remove `m_fields->m_pages` and use `m_iconPages` instead
- call `setupCustomPage` inside of `setupPage`
- make `onArrow` high priority, as it reimplements original now
- change `setupPage` priority from BeforePost to BeforePre, as the cursor was broken when swapping icons with Separate Dual Icons
- make `findIconPage` look for the SDI vanilla icon as well, although this technically doesn't change anything, as it only gets called when `setupCustomPage` is about to be called, so this probably doesn't need to be implemented on MI's end, but SDI's; I added it just to be sure, it should probably be removed
- remove `m_fields->m_onSelect` and use `GJGarageLayer::onSelect` directly; some mods, like my own, may completely remove every icon from the pages, so fetching the selector from it becomes impossible
- changed signatures of some methods to receive icon types as arguments instead of using `m_iconType`
- make SDI hooks call `selectTab` (which should re-setup the current page) instead of `setupCustomPage`

_ Nitpick (assertive)_

**Avoid redundant assertion with getAllByTestId; use queryAllByTestId or assert exact count**

getAllByTestId throws if there are zero matches, so the subsequent not.toHaveLength(0) is redundant. Prefer queryAllByTestId with a length check (presence), or assert an exact count if its deterministic.



Apply one of the following diffs:

- If you only need to assert presence of at least one date icon:

```diff
-    expect(screen.getAllByTestId('date-icon')).not.toHaveLength(0);
+    const dateIcons = screen.queryAllByTestId('date-icon');
+    expect(dateIcons.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
```

- If the UI deterministically renders a specific number (e.g., two icons for start/end):

```diff
-    expect(screen.getAllByTestId('date-icon')).not.toHaveLength(0);
+    expect(screen.getAllByTestId('date-icon')).toHaveLength(2);
```

issue.title: [Feature] Support The third argument of the lag/lead function supports non-const expr
issue.body:
## Why I'm doing:

Allow column expression (column name, arithmetic, function, etc.) to be used as the default value, aligning StarRocks with PostgreSQL, Oracle, and other major databases.

## What I'm doing:

Fixes #55865

### 2.1 Backend (BE)

| Area                        | Change                                                       |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **`LeadLagState`**          | Adds a `default_value_is_constant` flag.                     |
| **`LeadLagWindowFunction`** | *If* the default expression is a constant, follow the original fast path. *Else* evaluate the expression for each row. Fully supports `IGNORE NULLS` / non-`IGNORE NULLS`, and both lag/lead directions. |
| **Unit Tests**              | New tests `test_lag_without_ignore_nulls` and `test_lag_ignore_nulls` verify constant and column-name defaults. |



### 2.2 Frontend (FE)

| Area           | Change                                                       |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Analyzer**   | Removes the default must be constant restriction and validates general expressions. |
| **Unit Tests** | `AnalyzeFunctionTest#testLeadLagDefaultExpr` and `WindowTest#testLeadLagPlan`. |



### 2.3 Documentation

- Updates **English / Japanese / Chinese** window-function docs with an Example 3 that uses a column as the default value.

### 2.4 SQL Regression

- Adds a new regression suite `test_lead_lag/` covering forward / backward scans, with and without `IGNORE NULLS`.

## What type of PR is this:

- [ ] BugFix
- [x] Feature
- [ ] Enhancement
- [ ] Refactor
- [ ] UT
- [ ] Doc
- [ ] Tool

Does this PR entail a change in behavior?

- [ ] Yes, this PR will result in a change in behavior.
- [x] No, this PR will not result in a change in behavior.

README on kuvaava ja mys sovelluksen testaus on hyvin dokumentoitu. Kaikki 2. vlipalautuksen tavoitteet on toteutettu. Koodi nytt siistilt.

Sovelluksen kytettvyys on hyv. Asianmukaiset "Forbidden"- ja "Not found" -sivut ja erilaiset virhetilanteet (tyhjll tunnuksella + salasanalla kirjautuminen yms.) on otettu hyvin huomioon. Testailin sovellusta enk kertaakaan saanut sit kaatumaan. Mys ulkoasu on hyvll mallilla.

Jos lomakkeisiin sytt ei-kelvollista tietoa ja sivu uudelleenlatautuu ja nytt virheilmoituksen, kaikki lomakkeeseen sytetyt tiedot katoavat. Kyttjn kannalta olisi mukavaa, jos tiedot silyisivt kentiss.

Muita pieni seikkoja joita huomasin: arvostelua muokatessa on mahdollista laittaa katsomispiv tulevaisuuteen. Rivivlitys ei myskn toimi kommenteissa. Kyttjn omaa sivua voisi ehk muokata niin, ett "Arvostelut"-otsikko on piilotettu, jos kyttjll ei ole arvosteluja?

Sek valmiiden ett omien genrejen listankym toimii hyvin. Validointia on hoidettu hyvin sek HTML:ss ett Python-koodissa. Kommentin lisyksest palvelinpuolen validointi tosin nyttisi puuttuvan?

Hyv tyt!
